OL,3,CConcerns raised over ALN funding in
OL,4,CWelsh schools as demand expected to
OL,5,Cincrease
OL,7,F"Reforms to the ALN system in recent
OL,8,Fyears have been well-intentioned, but
OL,9,Freally poorly thought through in
OL,10,Fplaces, and not supported by enough
OL,11,Ffunding to ensure that schools can
OL,12,Fconsistently deliver the support
OL,13,Fpupils need."
OL,15,FThe shortfall in funding is also
OL,16,Fputting pressure on local government.
OL,17,FNeath Port Talbot Council already
OL,18,Fdirectly spends #18 million a year on
OL,19,FALN provision but has proposed a #7
OL,20,Fmillion increase in its next draft
OL,21,Fbudget to meet the demand.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
